Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drop @cream cheese{4%tablespoon}(in packets) into a small #bowl{} of warm water to soften.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(trimmed and halved lengthwise); cut crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Dice @tomato{1}(diced into ½-inch pieces). Quarter @lemon{1}.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a #baking sheet{}. Bake until golden brown and crispy, ~{7-9%minutes}. (For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between two baking sheets; toast on top and middle racks.)

Open package of @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{3%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and zucchini; season with @salt{} and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}. Set aside.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Use pan used for chicken.

Remove cream cheese packets from bowl; discard water and wipe bowl dry. Combine cream cheese and @Vidalia onion paste{1/2%ounce} in same bowl; whisk until smooth and creamy.

Place @arugula{2%ounce} and tomato in a large bowl. Add juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4 servings) and a drizzle of olive oil (large drizzle for 4). Season with pepper and toss to combine.

Evenly spread flatbreads with Vidalia cream and top with veggies. Cut into squares and divide between plates; top with arugula salad. Serve.